10. Risk Assessment

10.1 Risk: Over-Romanticisation of Human Cooking

Some human cooking is bad. Some is negligent. Some is actively hostile. The Ministry recognises that human intent does not guarantee culinary success.

Mitigation: distinguish between human judgement and human incompetence, while acknowledging that they often share a kitchen.

10.2 Risk: Underestimating Machine Capability

Machines will improve. Sensors will become more refined. AI systems may better model taste, preference, timing, and substitution.

Mitigation: continue reminding stakeholders that modelling care is not identical to caring.

10.3 Risk: Commercial Misuse of the Word “Homemade”

The term “homemade” may be applied to products assembled in facilities the size of airports.

Mitigation: establish the Protected Designation of Actual Someone There.

10.4 Risk: Excessive Gordon Ramsay Deployment

Sustained exposure to culinary outrage may destabilise committee morale.

Mitigation: restrict fury consultations to three per quarter, with optional bleeping.

